;s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 09 Oct 2010 15:15:43 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"1731590@http://wordpress.org/support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:343:\"<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>Just started writing my blog, and this may be a simple question but it is one that has been niggling at me for some time.</p>\n<p>I have a multi-author blog, how do we get the authors name to show when posting.</p>\n<p>I have been searching the settings but cannot find anything to turn them on... the names not the authors ;)\n</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"wwinegarden\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:17;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"\n			\n			\n			\n			\n			\n			\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"adeptris on \"Child theme with other images\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/child-theme-with-other-images#post-1716475\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 29 Sep 2010 20:54:24 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"1716475@http://wordpress.org/support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:782:\"<p>A quick look at the theme and the header image is called with a function in the functions.php file <code>lw_header_image()</code>.</p>\n<p><code>&#60;span id=&#34;top&#34; style=&#34;background:url(&#039;&#60;?php echo $top_header_image_path; ?&#62;&#039;)</code></p>\n<p>Untested but try first:<br />\n<pre><code>#top{\n   url(images/content_top.png) !important;\n}</code></pre>\n<p>Or in your child theme in the functions.php file you could overwrite the setting.</p>\n<pre><code>/* Change the path for the header image */\nfunction change_custom_header(){\n	$top_header_image_path = get_bloginfo(&#039;stylesheet_directory&#039;).&#34;/images/header-image.png&#34;;\n}\nadd_action( &#039;after_setup_theme&#039;, &#039;change_custom_header&#039; );</code></pre>\n<p>HTH </p>\n<p>David\n</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"adeptris\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:18;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"\n			\n			\n			\n			\n			\n			\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"adeptris on \"Child theme with other images\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/child-theme-with-other-images#post-1716423\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 29 Sep 2010 20:30:21 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"1716423@http://wordpress.org/support/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1188:\"<p>Check the parent themes style.css and see if the image is in the file.</p>\n<p>If it might be in code, being <strong>loaded in the header.php</strong>, if it is then copy the header.php from the parent to the child folder.</p>\n<p><strong>Only any linked images or files you want to call from the child theme</strong>.<br />\nWhere you might see:<br />\n<code>get_bloginfo(&#039;template_directory&#039;)</code><br />\nchange to:<br />\n<code>get_bloginfo(&#039;stylesheet_directory&#039;)</code></p>\n<p>Where you might see:<br />\n<code>TEMPLATEPATH</code><br />\nchange to<br />\n<code>STYLESHEETPATH</code></p>\n<p>The images you want called from the parent will still be called from the template path, the images you want from the child are called from the stylesheet path.</p>\n<p><strong>Example Child Theme Calls</strong></p>\n<pre><code>$imagepath = STYLESHEETPATH .&#039;/images/&#039;;\n$imageurl = get_bloginfo(&#039;stylesheet_directory&#039;) .&#039;/images/&#039;;\nif (file_exists(STYLESHEETPATH. &#039;/theme-options.php&#039;)) include_once ( STYLESHEETPATH . &#039;/theme-options.php&#039; );</code></pre>\n<p>Not that \'special\' once you are used to it.</p>\n<p>HTH</p>\n<p>David\n</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32: