 christian life that the idea came to me. \r\n\r\nI work in a business park that has lots and lots of different companies, while I don\'t know any Christians that work for my company, surely there must be some in the company next door. If I could meet with other Christians once a week, we could help support each other in prayer and build each other up.','Genesis','','inherit','open','open','','24-revision-9','','','2010-11-08 21:08:23','2010-11-08 21:08:23','',24,'http://prayer.funky-si.co.uk/2010/11/08/24-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(58,1,'2010-11-08 21:15:10','2010-11-08 21:15:10','<h2>GENESIS: The coming into being of something; the origin</h2>\r\nThe genesis of this idea goes back to April 2010. At that time I went to a Church weekend run by St Michael le Belfrey, the theme of the weekend was transformation, I heard some very interesting talks and seminars and found myself thinking what can I do to start a mini transformation.\r\n\r\nAt the same time I was getting very frustrated at how un-christian I felt during my working day, and wishing that I could be a better christian.\r\n\r\nLater in the year I went to a christian summer conference called <a href=\"http://www.new-wine.org/\">New Wine</a>, again I heard a lot about transformation and what small churches were doing to improve their communities. It was during this week, while immersed in the christian life that the idea came to me. \r\n\r\nI work in a business park that has lots and lots of different companies, while I don\'t know any Christians that work for my company, surely there must be some in the company next door. If I could meet with other Christians once a week, we could help support each other in prayer and build each other up.\r\n\r\nAfter I had the idea it was time to decide what to do to implement it. I spoke to various people from church which gave me some possible contacts. I then met with a couple of them at one of their homes, until we decided that a public venue would be better and less intimidating.','Genesis','','inherit','open','open','','24-revision-10','','','2010-11-08 21:15:10','2010-11-08 21:15:10','',24,'http://prayer.funky-si.co.uk/2010/11/08/24-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(59,1,'2010-11-08 21:44:36','2010-11-08 21:44:36','The following companies all have people who regularly come to our prayer meetings. If you want to come along I will happily put your website here. One of the side benefits of meeting together is that we get to know each other better and there may be opportunities to help each others businesses.\n\nI work for <a href=\"www.eurosafeuk.co.uk\">Eurosafe UK</a> They are a health and safety consultancy company specialising in Asbestos surveys, Construction Projects and IT services for the Construction Industry. This led them to release a range of cloud computing products called <a href=\"www.cloudsuk.com\">Clouds UK</a> \n\nAlan Brown runs a successful Financial Services Company <a href=\"http://www.sjpp.co.uk/alanbrown/index.html\">Brown\'s Wealth Management</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.tenpin.co.uk/\">Tenpin Bowling</a> is the bowling alley in Clifton Moor where we meet each week. Please pray for the staff there and that we can continue meeting here.\n\nThis group is not tied to one church or any denomination, all who want to meet and pray are welcome. We do have links with the following churches because members of the group worship their.\n<a href=\"http://www.stmichaelsyork.org/\">St Michael le Belfrey</a>\nClifton Parish Church','Useful Links','','inherit','open','open','','11-autosave','','','2010-11-08 21:44:36','2010-11-08 21:44:36','',11,'http://prayer.funky-si.co.uk/2010/11/08/11-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(60,1,'2010-11-08 12:50:02','2010-11-08 12:50:02','','Useful Links','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-3','','','2010-11-08 12:50:02','2010-11-08 12:50:02','',11,'http://prayer.funky-si.co.uk/2010/11/08/11-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(61,1,'2010-11-08 21:26:43','2010-11-08 21:26:43','The foll