r\n\r\nThe Alpha course is open to everyone interested in discovering what Christianity is about. Guests do Alpha for a wide variety of reasons - some want to investigate whether God exists; others are concerned about what happens after death. Some people have particular questions that they would like to discuss; others want to understand other peoples\' beliefs or would like to explore what the purpose of life is. Many guests have never been to church, others may have attended church occasionally but feel they have never really understood the basics of the Christian faith.\r\n\r\nAn Alpha course is currently running at <a href=\"http://www.stmichaelsyork.org/alpha.html\">St Michael le Belfrey</a> and a member of our Group is helping with the <a href=\"http://www.cliftonparish.org.uk/alpha/index.html\">Clifton Parish Church</a> Alpha Course. Today is actually the holy spirit weekend for the St Mikes course so I pray that they have a really blessed time and that many come to faith.\r\n\r\nA friend of mine has been called to lead a Global Alpha Training (GAT) team to Burundi in Januray. If alpha is a passion of your as well please consider look at and donating to <a href=\"http://www.justgiving.com/gatburundi\">http://www.justgiving.com/gatburundi</a> ','The Alpha Course','','publish','open','open','','the-alpha-course','','','2010-11-20 16:38:21','2010-11-20 16:38:21','',0,'http://www.prayer4work.com/?p=105',0,'post','',0),(86,1,'2010-11-13 09:11:51','2010-11-13 09:11:51','On Sunday 11th at 7pm Simon Foster was baptised in St Michael le Belfrey church York. Simon Foster also known as Funky Si to many of his friends, went on an alpha course in October 2008, this completely changed his view on religion, church and christianity. Before that he was a non-believer or athiest, now he is a regular church goer. To celebrate this change he has decided to affirm his faith with a full immersion baptism.\r\n\r\n<object classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" width